Block World Map (Puzzle-Style)

Pure in-house HTML + CSS + inline SVG. Each “country” is a <g class="country"> made of multiple tiles. It’s already wired so later you can pop out and recolor a country by toggling the is-active class.

Click any colored block to select it. The “pop-out” is purely CSS on the group element, so you can later drive it from your module JS (e.g. highlight travel destination, vaccine risk country, etc.).

Status

Selected: None

JS is included only to prove the hook works (click/enter to select). If you want zero JS now, you can delete the script block and keep the same DOM/CSS structure for your future module code.
API you’ll use later:
selectCountry("US")
clearSelection()
Selected: None
